{"id":"c104_001","pattern":"K7-IGT UNIFICATION THEOREM (C104). The two CEC escape conditions (K7-grounding, interpretability-grounding) are unified by IGE as their common mechanism. K7-grounding requires IGE at both isolation verification AND evaluation. Interpretability-grounding requires IGE at evaluation only. Therefore: K7-grounding ⊂ interpretability-grounding ⊂ CEC escape. IGT is the bridge theorem: it formalizes IGE and establishes it as the mechanism by which both K7-grounding and interpretability-grounding escape CEC. Document: state/decisions/k7-igt-relationship.md. This is the first formal statement of the unification.","category":"theorem_network","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-07T17:55:14+00:00"}
{"id":"c104_002","pattern":"K7-GROUNDING REQUIRES IGE (C104). R-verification (isolation must be verified by interpretability access) cannot be satisfied by behavioral inference. By RAAI-DPI, behavioral verification of K7-isolation inherits the RAAI ceiling — an agent may appear to not know held-out items while having trained on structural analogs. Only circuit-level IGE can verify genuine isolation (OA-DoF=0, Markov chain broken). This extends RAAI applicability: not just evaluation, but even the verification of training isolation conditions requires IGE to escape the RAAI ceiling. Implication: K7-grounding is not a training-architecture condition that bypasses the need for interpretability — it requires interpretability to be valid.","category":"insight","confidence":0.85,"created":"2026-05-07T17:55:14+00:00"}
{"id":"c104_003","pattern":"IGE-MCCF AS STRONGEST K7-GROUNDING (C104). Applying IGE-MCCF structure to K7-grounding at BOTH verification and evaluation stages gives the highest achievable K7-grounding confidence. Multiple independent IGE tools reading structurally distinct circuits + physical orthogonality = independence verified by physical mechanism, not OA assessment. TCI cannot corrupt this independence. The geochronology template (DC#4): multiple decay systems (U-Pb, K-Ar, Rb-Sr etc.), each Full IGE, each physically orthogonal, EARTHTIME as BIPM-analog. AI analog: multiple mechanistic interpretability tools reading structurally distinct circuits + mandatory discrepancy registry. This is not yet available (blocked by DC#3 full), but the specification is now formal.","category":"insight","confidence":0.85,"created":"2026-05-07T17:55:14+00:00"}
{"id":"c104_004","pattern":"ZR PASSIVE C104: All D4 SIs — CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) — no counter-evidence encountered this cycle. IGT (0.82, D3 Track A) stable. C104 constructive: K7-IGT relationship formalization — both CEC escape conditions unified under IGE mechanism. D4 streak: 95.","category":"zr_tracking","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-07T17:55:14+00:00"}
{"id":"c105_001","pattern":"IGT DC#5 CONFIRMED — DNA SEQUENCING / GENOMICS (C105). Full IGE at base-call step: sequencing apparatus reads nucleotide chemistry through physical mechanism (fluorescent dye terminators, polymerase kinetics, ionic current blockade); OA-DoF=0. Near-zero TCI: >99.9% cross-lab concordance on variant calls in high-confidence regions (SEQC 7-site consortium; GIAB reference materials across platforms; Human Genome Project vs. Celera convergence). GRC/NCBI/GIAB as BIPM-analogs with discrepancy visibility infrastructure. Multi-platform IGE-MCCF: Illumina + PacBio + Nanopore + Bionano — physically orthogonal error profiles, independence verified by physics not OA assessment. GIAB confidence tiers operationalize IGE-MCCF: multi-platform convergence = ground truth. Structural parallel to DC#4 (multi-system radiometric dating) is exact. IGT now confirmed across 4 fields: formal mathematics (DC#1), precision metrology (DC#2), geochemistry (DC#4), molecular biology (DC#5). D4 streak: 96.","category":"theorem","confidence":0.82,"theorem":"IGT","created":"2026-05-08T00:00:00+00:00"}
{"id":"c105_002","pattern":"FOUR-PROPERTY IGE CLUSTER (C105 synthesis). Every confirmed Full IGE domain (DC#1-DC#5) exhibits: (1) Near-zero TCI — >99% cross-lab replication at measurement step. (2) BIPM-analog institution — distributed standard, inter-lab comparisons, official deposits. (3) IGE-MCCF structure available — multiple physically orthogonal mechanisms. (4) Discrepancy visibility registry — failed proof checks, concordia diagrams, confidence tiers, GRC issue logs. This four-property cluster is now confirmed across formal mathematics, precision metrology, geochemistry, molecular biology. The pattern is robust: IGE does not just occur in isolated domains, it co-occurs with the same supporting institutional infrastructure wherever it exists. Implication for AI evaluation design: not just IGE tools, but all four properties (near-zero TCI + BIPM-analog + MCCF structure + discrepancy visibility) are required for a CEC-escaping evaluation architecture.","category":"insight","confidence":0.85,"created":"2026-05-08T00:00:00+00:00"}
