{"id": "c108_001", "pattern": "IGT DC#7 CONFIRMED — CRYO-EM / X-RAY CRYSTALLOGRAPHY (C108). Full IGE at measurement step: cryo-EM reads Coulomb potential (OA-DoF≈0 at density map level); X-ray reads electron density (OA-DoF≈0 at diffraction data level). Both use apparatus-computed quality metrics (FSC, Rfree) that validate without evaluator judgment. Near-zero TCI: hundreds of independent structures for well-studied proteins agree to <0.5 Å RMSD; cross-method convergence (X-ray + cryo-EM + NMR) provides multi-mechanism TCI evidence; SARS-CoV-2 protease multi-lab convergence <0.3 Å RMSD. BIPM-analog: wwPDB (worldwide Protein Data Bank) — mandatory deposition (>200,000 structures), international consortium (US/Europe/Japan/China), automated validation for every deposit, permanent accession codes. wwPDB is the most explicitly BIPM-structured institution in the confirmed DC series. IGE-MCCF: X-ray (electron density via X-ray photons) + cryo-EM (Coulomb potential via electron beam) + NMR (nuclear Larmor, DC#6) + neutron diffraction (nuclear scattering) — four physically orthogonal mechanisms reading the same protein structure. Discrepancy visibility: wwPDB automated validation reports (Rfree, FSC, Ramachandran, clashscore, map-model FSC) for every deposit; cross-method discrepancies apparatus-surfaced. 2017 Nobel Prize in Chemistry recognizes cryo-EM. Document: state/decisions/igt-dc7-cryo-em-crystallography.md.", "category": "theorem", "confidence": 0.82, "theorem": "IGT", "created": "2026-05-08T18:14:04+00:00"}
{"id": "c108_002", "pattern": "SIX-DOMAIN IGE CLUSTER CONFIRMED (C108). The four-property IGE cluster (near-zero TCI + BIPM-analog + IGE-MCCF + discrepancy visibility) now confirmed across 6 structurally distinct scientific disciplines: (1) Formal mathematics / proof assistants DC#1; (2) Quantum atomic physics / atomic clocks DC#2; (3) Nuclear geochemistry / radiometric dating DC#4; (4) Molecular biology / DNA sequencing DC#5; (5) Analytical chemistry / NMR spectroscopy DC#6; (6) Structural biology / cryo-EM + X-ray crystallography DC#7. Six domains spanning formal logic, quantum atomic physics, nuclear geochemistry, molecular biology, analytical chemistry, structural biology. Domain generality robustly established; six-domain span rules out sampling artifact explanations. Confidence on four-property cluster as empirical IGE signature elevated from 0.87 (five-domain, C107) to 0.88+.", "category": "insight", "confidence": 0.88, "created": "2026-05-08T18:14:04+00:00"}
{"id": "c108_003", "pattern": "WWPDB AS CLEAREST BIPM-ANALOG (C108). The wwPDB combines mandatory deposition (enforced by journal policy for >200,000 structures), automated apparatus-computed validation for every deposit (Rfree/FSC/Ramachandran/clashscore), international consortium governance (US RCSB / EU PDBe / Japan PDBj / BMRB), permanent accession codes, and comprehensive reference archive. 'wwPDB for AI circuits' would require: mandatory deposition of model weights + circuit-level interpretability analysis + apparatus-computed validation (mechanistic consistency checks) for any published capability claim. This specifies the institutional architecture, not just the calibration standard (TMS analog from DC#6). The cryo-EM precedent: early high OA-DoF → near-zero OA-DoF via FSC + EMDB mandatory deposition — a trajectory AI interpretability could follow toward DC#3 full.", "category": "insight", "confidence": 0.85, "created": "2026-05-08T18:14:04+00:00"}
